# ASP.NET Core Identity API Testing

This file demonstrates how to test the Identity endpoints provided by the Users module.

## Register a new user

POST https://localhost:7299/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password": "Test123!"
}

### 

## Login

POST https://localhost:7299/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com", 
  "password": "Test123!"
}

### 

## Get user profile (requires authentication)
# Copy the accessToken from the login response and use it in the Authorization header

GET https://localhost:7299/api/users/profile
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

###

## Get all users (requires authentication)  
# Copy the accessToken from the login response and use it in the Authorization header

GET https://localhost:7299/api/users
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

###

## Logout

POST https://localhost:7299/logout
Content-Type: application/json

###